00:40:30.710 --> 00:40:34.370
And the copper cathode
had copper solid being

00:40:34.370 --> 00:40:36.140
plated onto it.

00:40:36.140 --> 00:40:39.530
So Faraday's law
says that the amount

00:40:39.530 --> 00:40:43.460
in which an anode, like
the zinc anode, is consumed

00:40:43.460 --> 00:40:47.870
and the amount of copper that
gets plated on at the cathode

00:40:47.870 --> 00:40:51.020
is proportional to the charge
that passes through the system.

00:40:51.020 --> 00:40:53.010
So according to
Faraday's law, there

00:40:53.010 --> 00:40:56.540
is a proportionality
between the consumption

00:40:56.540 --> 00:41:01.520
and also depositing of metal
and the amount of charge

00:41:01.520 --> 00:41:03.080
going through the system.

00:41:03.080 --> 00:41:07.790
So we can think about
how much zinc is consumed

00:41:07.790 --> 00:41:15.230
and how much copper is deposited
on its cathode or its electrode

00:41:15.230 --> 00:41:19.430
if you have a current of
1 amp flowing for 1 hour.

00:41:19.430 --> 00:41:22.700
So let's just take a look at
how we do a problem like this.

00:41:22.700 --> 00:41:25.220
First step is we
want to think about,

00:41:25.220 --> 00:41:29.100
calculate the charge that's
going through the system.

00:41:29.100 --> 00:41:33.710
And so Q here, we have another
