00:41:33.710 --> 00:41:35.330
but the magnitude of the charge.

00:41:35.330 --> 00:41:37.160
And that's in coulombs.

00:41:37.160 --> 00:41:40.620
And that's going to be equal
to the current times the time.

00:41:40.620 --> 00:41:44.210
So we have the current, I.
And the current is in amps.

00:41:44.210 --> 00:41:45.950
And t is in seconds.

00:41:45.950 --> 00:41:49.860
And conveniently, amps
equal coulombs per second.

00:41:49.860 --> 00:41:51.350
So this equation works out.

00:41:51.350 --> 00:41:53.540
Our units will work out.

00:41:53.540 --> 00:41:58.580
So Q is going to be equal
to-- we have 1.0 amps.

00:41:58.580 --> 00:42:02.720
And it was 1 hour, so
that's 3,600 seconds,

00:42:02.720 --> 00:42:09.620
or 3,600 coulombs, because
we have an amp times second.

00:42:09.620 --> 00:42:14.180
And then here, we have
this number of coulombs.

00:42:14.180 --> 00:42:17.690
And now we want to convert
to the number of moles

00:42:17.690 --> 00:42:21.620
of electrons that that is
equivalent to, that that charge

00:42:21.620 --> 00:42:23.690
in coulombs is equivalent to.

00:42:23.690 --> 00:42:28.280
